25/07/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- President Bamir Topi welcomed on Thursday (July 24th) Macedonia's ratification of a decision abolishing visas for Albanian citizens. 
Under the measure, approved by parliament Tuesday, citizens of both Albania and Macedonia can stay for 90 days within a six-month period on the other country's territory. 
Those living within 20km of the border can enter the neighbouring country showing ID cards.
In other news Thursday, Albanian lawmakers adopted a bill providing 164m euros in supplementary budget funds for the rest of the year. 
The additional money will improve road infrastructure, cover the annual budget deficit and fund local administration. 
(TVSH, Alsat, INA, Makfax, Top Channel, BalkanWeb, BBC, Top Channel, Telegrafi - 24/07/08)
